description:
Proper Japanese Title: ジャンプGIGA

Jump Giga was an extremely short-lived special issue spin-off of Weekly Shonen Jump. Notably, though it was meant to replace the line of special issues of Shonen Jump that has gone through a number of changes (see: Weekly Shonen Jump Special, Akamaru Jump and Jump Next!), it was published more frequently than any of those ever were.

From the first issue Giga has already started a number of ongoing serials, as opposed to one-shots taking up most of the magazine like its predecessors (though it still has more one-shots than a standard manga magazine). However, like its predecessors it does focus on using popular series from the main magazine to promote itself, featuring the established works all over the cover when the new material is actually the bulk of the magazine.

As the magazine ended after only four issues to prepare for yet another rebranding, several of the four chapter serials were collected (with four monthly chapters being the ideal length for a tankobon release).
name: Shonen Jump GIGA
